description.narrative:
The objective of the contracted consultancy is helping to implement the Support to the Civil Society in Ukraine Programme by: undertaking system-based audits of CSOs coupled with capacity development work, while providing mentoring, training and coaching services to the Ukrainian programme- and project-supported NGOs to facilitate their strategies implementation and result-based management.

Besides, the consultancy is engaged in spearheading Swedish perspectives and development effectiveness - namely, the overarching poor peoples perspectives, the rights perspective, as well as the thematic perspectives of environment and climate, gender equality, and conflict.

The assignment pursues consultancy services in the areas of organizational effectiveness, organizational development, capacity enhancement, monitoring and evaluation, and implementation follow-up for the Embassys partner CSOs (both current and prospective) along the lines of these objectives:

- Pre-selection and verification;
- Implementation follow-up, mentorship and advisory support; 
- Perspectives to mainstream development effectiveness; 
- Monitoring and evaluation;
- Other specific task/s aimed at networking, sharing of NGO good practices, peer exchange, etc.
